Depending on the half-lives of the
products of interest, the irradiations had a duration
of approximately 7 h, 1 h, or 3 min. Following
irradiation, the target and monitor discs were
separately assayed with calibrated Ge(Li) gamma-ray
spectrometers, intrinsic Ge x-ray spectrometers, or
in the case of the carbon monitor foils, with a NaI
iodine and xenon products were identified by their
characteristic gamma rays or x rays and half-lives.
The targets consisted of KI pellets made by
compressing the powder to a thickness of ~120 mg/cm2.
They were circular, had a diameter of 1.5 cm, and
were mechanically stable and of good uniformity
(~2%). The target stack consisted of a pellet
